\[\mathbb{E}\left[\tilde{y}_{t}^{\overline{x}}|\mathcal{F}_{t-1}\right] =t_{t}^{\overline{x}}\times\left(2B_{y}\int_{-B_{y}}^{B_{y}} \mathbb{P}\left[u\leq y_{t}|\mathcal{F}_{t-1}\right]\frac{\mathrm{d}u}{2B_{y} }-B_{y}\right)\] \[=t_{t}^{\overline{x}}\times\left(\int_{-B_{y}}^{B_{y}}\int_{-B_{t }}^{B_{t}}\mathds{1}\left\{u\leq g(x_{t})+\xi\right\}f(\xi)\,\mathrm{d}\xi\, \mathrm{d}u-B_{y}\right)\] \[=t_{t}^{\overline{x}}\times\left(\int_{-B_{t}}^{B_{t}}\int_{-B_{y }}^{\xi+g(x_{t})}\mathrm{d}uf(\xi)\,\mathrm{d}\xi-B_{y}\right)\] \[=t_{t}^{\overline{x}}\times\left(g(x_{t})+\int_{-B_{t}}^{B_{t}} \xi f(\xi)\,\mathrm{d}\xi\right)\] \[=\tilde{g}_{t}^{\overline{x}}\]

where in the last equality we used that \(\int_{-B_{t}}^{B_{t}}\xi f(\xi)\,\mathrm{d}\xi=\mathbb{E}\left[\xi_{t}\right]=0\). The same relation also trivially holds when \(t_{t}^{\overline{x}}=0\). Thus, conditionally on \(\mathcal{F}_{t-1}\), \(\tilde{y}_{t}-\tilde{y}_{t}^{\overline{x}}\) is centered and in \([-B_{y},B_{y}]\). We denote \(N_{t}^{\overline{x}}=\sum_{s<t}t_{s}^{\overline{x}}\), we note that if \(t\notin\mathcal{G}^{\overline{x}}\), then \(N_{t}^{\overline{x}}=\lceil\tau\rceil\) a.s. Using Lemma 12, we find that for all \(t\notin\mathcal{G}^{\overline{x}}\), a.s., \(N_{t}^{\overline{x}}=\lceil\tau\rceil\). Then,

